    "block_type": "text",
    "text": "4.2 Evaluation Metrics We adopt accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score as our evaluation metrics. The metrics are computed from two perspectives: the CVE level (accuracy) and the version level (precision, recall, and F1-score). Specifically, at the CVE level, an identification is labeled True only if the set of vulnerable versions exactly matches the ground truth. All other CVEs are labeled False. At the version level, each identified version is individually compared against the ground truth. A version present in the ground truth is counted as a TP; a version not present is counted as an FP; and a version that exists in the ground truth but is not identified is counted as an FN. The evaluation metrics are calculated as follows:",
